always keeling over.

807
01:17:28,042 --> 01:17:30,602
I never know
whether she's playing possum or not.

808
01:17:31,712 --> 01:17:33,771
How can you live
with a woman like that?

809
01:17:33,948 --> 01:17:36,644
Oh, it was the face that trapped me.

810
01:17:36,817 --> 01:17:39,377
I thought I could
make something out of her, but...

811
01:17:39,820 --> 01:17:41,685
It's <i>imposible.</i>

812
01:17:41,856 --> 01:17:47,055
There's nothing you can do
with this poor white trash.

813
01:17:50,264 --> 01:17:53,097
Poor white trash.

814
01:17:55,402 --> 01:17:58,371
Poor white trash.

815
01:17:58,539 --> 01:18:02,805
I guess that's what I am.
But the world is full of trash.

816
01:18:02,977 --> 01:18:05,969
High fancy trash and low filthy trash.

817
01:18:06,146 --> 01:18:08,410
Now hold your tongue, woman.

818
01:18:08,582 --> 01:18:12,780
My dear husband, my lover, my hero.

819
01:18:12,953 --> 01:18:16,184
All that mushmouth talk
about your precious honor.

820
01:18:16,357 --> 01:18:20,123
Back home, sure, you waved it around
like the Confederate flag.

821
01:18:20,294 --> 01:18:21,818
You even challenged a man once...

822
01:18:21,996 --> 01:18:24,464
...when he said his hound dog
was better than yours.

823
01:18:24,632 --> 01:18:26,964
And what has this lout done to you?

824
01:18:27,134 --> 01:18:32,128
